On the other hand, it is also easier to retract the phallus by pulling a unique central structure. However, we believe that a second component facilitates the phallus retraction, the processes mp.dl . These processes are located on the dorsalmost portion of the anterophallic face in both genera and are connected directly to the sclerite VS apex (in
Warimiri
gen. nov.
) or the processes ti (in
Hyperomerus
). We believe these processes act like tendons, pulling back inside the sclerite VS ( Fig. 1G , white arrow ). Ventrally, a membranous projection of the phallus is connected to the subgenital plate and acts like a frenulum, helping to retract the phallus ( Fig. 1F , white arrow ).
